<h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="details-title">Details</h2>


<div aria-labelledby="details-title">
  
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>This joint <abbr title="Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy">BEIS</abbr> / <abbr title="Office for Nuclear Regulation">ONR</abbr> guidance covers future reporting requirements for operators. These reporting requirements will allow the UK to comply with Nuclear Cooperation Agreements and other obligations arising from international trade following the UK’s withdrawal from the European Atomic Energy Community (Euratom).</p>

<p>The guidance covers a number of areas, including:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
<abbr title="Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy">BEIS</abbr> and <abbr title="Office for Nuclear Regulation">ONR</abbr>’s expectations on operators relating to relevant provisions of the <a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2019/196/contents/made">Nuclear Safeguards (EU Exit) Regulations 2019</a>
</li>
  <li>export licensing requirements</li>
</ul>

<p>It will take effect from:</p>

<ul>
  <li>1 November 2019 if the UK leaves the EU with no deal</li>
</ul>

<p>Or</p>

<ul>
  <li>1 January 2021 if a deal is reached with the EU (at the end of the implementation period)</li>
</ul>

<p>A previous version of this guidance, published on 27 June 2019, was open for comment until 31 August 2019.</p>

<div class="call-to-action">
<h2 id="stay-up-to-date">Stay up to date</h2>

<p>Get ready for Brexit on 31 October. This page tells you how to prepare for Brexit. It will be updated if anything changes, including if a deal is agreed.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/find-eu-exit-guidance-business/email-signup">Sign up for email alerts</a> to get the latest information.</p>
</div>

